data.title: 'FUBAR’ reprises Arnold Schwarzenegger one liners & dialogues; Here’s the full list of references
data.meta_description: Arnold Schwarzenegger fans are on cloud nine as they get to hear some of his iconic lines – all that in one work – FUBAR, thanks to showrunner and producer Nick Santora.
data.text:
Synopsis

Arnold Schwarzenegger fans are on cloud nine as they get to hear some of his iconic lines – all that in one work – FUBAR, thanks to showrunner and producer Nick Santora.

Arnold Schwarzenegger makes his scripted television debut with FUBAR. However, it's not just his return to television that has fans excited. FUBAR is filled with his famous catchphrase in True Lies, "That's it, and that's all," to the memorable lines from The Predator and The Terminator, FUBAR is packed with references to Schwarzenegger's blockbuster films.

The series, now streaming on Netflix, offers fans a chance to relive these classic quotes.

FUBAR showrunner and executive producer Nick Santora expressed his excitement about working on this “surreal project.” Growing up watching Schwarzenegger films, Santora felt privileged to create the actor's first scripted television project.

It's no wonder that this season is filled with nostalgic movie references, paying homage to Schwarzenegger's illustrious career.

Episode 1 – "Take Your Daughter To Work Day"

In the first episode, viewers are treated to an unmistakable homage to Schwarzenegger's role as The Terminator with “You can’t be true to two!”.

Episode 2 – “Stole Train”

This episode features the classic line, "Get to the Choppa!" from Predator. Hearing Schwarzenegger say those words again is sure to bring a smile to any fan's face.

Episode 4 – “Armed & Dane-gerous"

Schwarzenegger delivers a line reminiscent of his Terminator character, demanding, "I need your wallet and your gun."

Episode 6 – “Royally Flushed”

It doesn't include a direct quote, but Arnie's line, "You seem to be shocked to see me," invokes memories of his role as Mr. Freeze in Batman & Robin and his knack for ice-related one-liners.

Episode 8 – "That's It & That's All"

Here, Schwarzenegger references the "Choppa!" once again, showcasing his signature delivery. The episode's title itself is a nod to his latest catchphrase in the series, which he attributes to the film Throw Momma From The Train.

FAQs

How old is Arnold Schwarzenegger?

As of May 2023, he is 75 years old.

Where is Arnold Schwarzenegger from?

He was born in Thal, Styria, Austria.
